(6, 1725135337, 'How to Invite Amiibo Campers To Your Island...', '2020-08-17', 'Once you\'ve unlocked the campground, you can invite villagers to your island using Amiibo cards! The Amiibo function can be utilized at the Nook Stop inside Resident\'s Services.\r\n\r\nStep 1: Invite Amiibo camper!\r\nSimply click \"Invite a camper\", and you will be prompted to put the Amiibo over the right joystick. Once the camper is confirmed on the screen, you are ready to invite your camper!\r\n\r\nInvi', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Once you\'ve unlocked the campground, you can invite villagers to your island using Amiibo cards! The Amiibo function can be utilized at the&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Nook Stop</span>&nbsp;inside Resident\'s Services.</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Step 1: Invite Amiibo camper!</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Simply click \"Invite a camper\", and you will be prompted to put the Amiibo over the right joystick. Once the camper is confirmed on the screen, you are ready to invite your camper!</p><p><img alt=\"Inviting a camper\" src=\"https://images.ctfassets.net/ccpqjwcq0rmr/1uLUM9lvYG5CbVCDYJdo6x/380c84d3f19db8d4f50aa3bb975118d3/2020072719561500-02CB906EA538A35643C1E1484C4B947D.jpg\" style=\"width: 614.688px; margin: 0px 0px 0.8rem; border-style: none; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"></p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Step 2: Fulfill their request for an island souvenir...</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">As soon as you proceed through the dialog, the campsite villager will appear in the tent. When you enter and speak to them a few times, they will ask you for a souvenir and give you the DIY recipe if you do not yet have it.</p><p><img alt=\"Souvenir Request\" src=\"https://images.ctfassets.net/ccpqjwcq0rmr/4BDZZmPLkCNYb2inXzH7AZ/0d6b7401ff6b7706f7f66ba5771f0584/2020072721010200-02CB906EA538A35643C1E1484C4B947D.jpg\" style=\"width: 614.688px; margin: 0px 0px 0.8rem; border-style: none; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">You&nbsp;<i>must</i>&nbsp;make the souvenir and bring it back if you have any intention of inviting this villager to live on your island for good! In return, they will give you a present.</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Step 3: Repeat!</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">If you have any intention of inviting said Amiibo villager to live on your island, you can invite them back to your campsite as early as the next day! You need to&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">repeat steps 1 &amp; 2&nbsp;</span>for a total of&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">3 times</span>&nbsp;in order to invite the villager to stay for good.</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Step 4: Persuading the Amiibo villager to move in...</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">After you\'ve invited the Amiibo villager to your campsite, and given them a souvenir a&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">total of 3 times</span>, you can ask them to move in! Speak with them until it gives you the option to ask them to move to your island.</p><p><img alt=\"Asking villager to move in\" src=\"https://images.ctfassets.net/ccpqjwcq0rmr/6bfgUeJC4Brd5U3iFz88T9/e43bc4f053c6502c7882c7224fa0b93b/2020072721051500-02CB906EA538A35643C1E1484C4B947D.jpg\" style=\"width: 614.688px; margin: 0px 0px 0.8rem; border-style: none; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">They will then go ask&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Resident Services</span>&nbsp;if they are able to move to your island! But unfortunately, they will be turned down....</p><p><img alt=\"There\'s no room for a new villager!\" src=\"https://images.ctfassets.net/ccpqjwcq0rmr/4x4c40gbsDFMWrut8MCn15/6a6c6545a8ee1be0cbf265af2ed2520a/2020072721052700-02CB906EA538A35643C1E1484C4B947D.jpg\" style=\"width: 614.688px; margin: 0px 0px 0.8rem; border-style: none; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">However, you will then be prompted to&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">choose which villager you want to kick out to free up a spot!</span></p><p><img alt=\"Kicking out a villager\" src=\"https://images.ctfassets.net/ccpqjwcq0rmr/1Z8iqRsOovcvCmYT3YliMH/ab47ed2938d1147a2e0a793798844c85/2020072721061000-02CB906EA538A35643C1E1484C4B947D.jpg\" style=\"width: 614.688px; margin: 0px 0px 0.8rem; border-style: none; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">The second you confirm which villager you want to kick out, that villager will be in boxes!</p><p><img alt=\"Confirmation of kicking villager out\" src=\"https://images.ctfassets.net/ccpqjwcq0rmr/OgtdCe1bttCF6b64tSbSE/4c9006fca352d5deee2976d2826b8265/2020072721085400-02CB906EA538A35643C1E1484C4B947D.jpg\" style=\"width: 614.688px; margin: 0px 0px 0.8rem; border-style: none; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">And the very next day, the plot will be reserved for the campsite villager you invited using your Amiibo!</p><p><img alt=\"Reserved plot for Amiibo villager!!!\" src=\"https://images.ctfassets.net/ccpqjwcq0rmr/2O1ZgohpM73efAKOcuX0OI/4be709b4a392343c78665c0f00f9060d/2020072809523700-02CB906EA538A35643C1E1484C4B947D.jpg\" style=\"width: 614.688px; margin: 0px 0px 0.8rem; border-style: none; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">This is the&nbsp;<i><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">easiest</span></i>&nbsp;way to kick specific villagers out! It comes with a small price, but you should be able to easily find Amiibo cards/coins for cheap on Etsy or Amazon</p>'),
(7, 1725135449, 'What Summer Update Wave 2 Has to Offer...', '2020-07-28', 'It\'s here! Well, almost. The second wave of Animal Crossing: New Horizon\'s Summer Update will be available on July 30th! Here\'s what we know:\r\n\r\nFireworks\r\nFireworks\r\nScreenshot courtesy of Nintendo\r\nFireworks will light up your island\'s skies every Sunday in August at 7PM, in both the Northern and Southern Hemispheres. You can even launch custom design fireworks! There is a whole new way for Redd', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">It\'s here! Well, almost. The second wave of Animal Crossing: New Horizon\'s Summer Update will be available on&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">July 30th!&nbsp;</span>Here\'s what we know:</p><hr style=\"overflow: visible; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Fireworks</h3><p><img alt=\"Fireworks\" src=\"https://images.ctfassets.net/ccpqjwcq0rmr/i0uI9aDTjvJlQ8jiQyCA0/66878cb9f2579f9e5e217339ecf14345/Fireworks.jpg\" style=\"width: 614.688px; margin: 0px 0px 0.8rem; border-style: none; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Screenshot courtesy of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=InDJvcWtTCw\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(242, 190, 126);\">Nintendo</a></p><hr style=\"overflow: visible; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Fireworks will light up your island\'s skies every Sunday in August at 7PM, in both the Northern and Southern Hemispheres. You can even launch custom design fireworks! There is a whole new way for&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Redd</span>&nbsp;to scam you‚Äî at Redd\'s Raffle in the plaza, where you can redeem Bells for special prizes.</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Dreaming</h3><p><img alt=\"Dreaming\" src=\"https://images.ctfassets.net/ccpqjwcq0rmr/JkdXOVqzdZTVPGWOsOBuF/2d09c1f1057654610e40b3ff50a1e9de/Dreaming.jpg\" style=\"width: 614.688px; margin: 0px 0px 0.8rem; border-style: none; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Screenshot courtesy of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=InDJvcWtTCw\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(242, 190, 126);\">Nintendo</a></p><hr style=\"overflow: visible; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Special NPC Luna brings back the \"Dream Suite\" ! This time, players will be asked if they want to sleep when they lay down on a bed, and if so, Luna will appear! She acts as a dreamland spirit guide, taking you to other island\'s all over the world to explore as much as you\'d like.</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Island Backup Restoration Service</h3><p><img alt=\"Backups\" src=\"https://images.ctfassets.net/ccpqjwcq0rmr/7CdU01CBK2fL7QGUAa9oV5/67a9f73ae8a3fad1cd46210b567c5768/Backups.jpg\" style=\"width: 614.688px; margin: 0px 0px 0.8rem; border-style: none; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Screenshot courtesy of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=InDJvcWtTCw\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(242, 190, 126);\">Nintendo</a></p><hr style=\"overflow: visible; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Up until now, save data has been tied to your Nintendo Switch console. Meaning if it becomes lost or damaged‚Äî the long hard hours you spent perfecting your island would vanish into thin air.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">The new update comes with \"Island Backup Restoration Service\". Players can enable this service, which automatically uploads your island\'s and user save data to the internet \"at certain times.\" In order to retrieve the save data on a new Nintendo Switch, you\'ll have to call Nintendo Customer Support.</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">And for the future...</h3><p><img alt=\"FallUpdate\" src=\"https://images.ctfassets.net/ccpqjwcq0rmr/36BP599JXuzc6siRjyQpec/2e38c719f3aaa483521d1515efac0f88/FallUpdate.jpg\" style=\"width: 614.688px; margin: 0px 0px 0.8rem; border-style: none; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Screenshot courtesy of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=InDJvcWtTCw\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(242, 190, 126);\">Nintendo</a></p><hr style=\"overflow: visible; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);\">Nintendo also hinted at a free&nbsp;<i>Halloween</i>&nbsp;update available this Fall!</p>');

